./" This is the manpage for the Simple Shell program
.TH _shell 1 "28 April 2023" "1.0" "Program Manual for Simple Shell"                                     
.SH NAME
simple_shell - a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a simple UNIX command interpreter that reads commands from standard input or from a script file and executes them. It provides a basic set of features, such as command execution, variable substitution, and piping. It also supports environment variables, signal handling, and simple built-in commands.


.SH OPTIONS
None

.SH COMMANDS
The following commands are supported by simple_shell:

.IP exit
Exit the shell with the specified status code (or 0 if none is provided).

.IP env 
Print the current environment.

All commands that are found in your local /bin, such as ls, echo, ps. 

.SH EXAMPLES
To execute a command:

$ echo "Hello, World!"

"Hello, World!"

To execute a script file:

$ ./my_script.sh

